todos.title: Find DFT indices for the Carrier Frequency and Tolerance
todos.notes:
% find exact carrier frequency
fc = 60000 % Hz ----- I have been incrementing this value to try and find the proper frequencies.
tol = 1000; % Hz

% Calculate ind_c and ind_tol in terms of fc and tol
% Hint: Make sure you understand how ind_c and ind_tol are used in
% getPeak.m
df = Fs/N
ind_c = round(fc/df) + (N+1)/2; % <-- Index corresponding to fc (integer)
ind_tol = round(tol / df) % <-- Index corresponding to tol (integer)

ind_i = getPeak(X_IQ, ind_c, ind_tol); % Make sure you have this function in the workspace
f_i = freq_x(ind_i) %frequency corresponding to peak index

% Demodulate message to account for inexact carrier frequency

% Complete the following line of code and uncomment to run
n = 0:N-1
s = exp(-j*2*pi*f_i*n/Fs); % <--- complex sinusoid corresponding to exact carrier
x_b = real(x_IQ.*s);
real(s(10000))
imag(s(20000))

% Complete the following line of code and uncomment to run
a = filter(h,1,x_b); % <--- apply lowpass filter

% Play demodulated signal
soundsc(a,Fs)

events.title: Talk by Nan Chen: Introduction to Uncertainty Quantification
events.notes: Abstract: I will provide a tutorial on uncertainty quantification (UQ) for those with no background but interested in learning more about this area. The talk will use many elementary examples understandable to undergraduates to present the ideas of UQ. Topics include characterizing uncertainties using information theory, UQ in linear and nonlinear dynamical systems, UQ via data, and the role of uncertainty in diagnostics. These examples explain why and how UQ is essential. Both MATLAB and Python codes have been made available for these simple examples. There will be pizza provided.

todos.title: WiTri- Strength Workout 3
todos.notes: There is not an official team strength workout as a group, but this can be done on your own or w/training partner(s) on your own time. Does not have to be on Wednesday, can be on whatever day fits your schedule the best. If any questions about proper lifting technique for specific a specific exercise, do not attempt if unsure on technique to avoid risking injury. Ask coach or other team member who is experienced with lifting. Amount of weight used should be challenging on the last few reps but not maxing out- do not risk failure. If unsure of how much weight to use, start on the conservative/lighter side, and increase from there as you feel able. Description: ~5 minute warmup- either choice aerobic exercise or a variety of body weight exercises; ~5 minutes light stretching; 3x6 of the following exercises: -RDL or trap bar deadlift -Pullups or lat pull downs -Calf raises -Single arm dumbbell chest press; 8 core exercises of choice- 45 seconds on/15 seconds rest for each; ~5min stretching. Total duration: 1 hour.

events.title: CFD Simulation for Mixing Vessels: Faster with the New Ansys App
events.notes: The Ansys CFD Mixing App enables faster and easier flow and mixing calculations. Join to understand the capabilities and usability of the new Ansys App.

events.title: A Comprehensive Introduction to the Simulation Ecosystem for Photonic ICs
events.notes: Photonic Integrated Circuits (PICs) design uses a comprehensive simulation framework for device optimization, circuit simulation, and system validation across various applications, including LiDAR and quantum photonics.

events.title: Ansys Optics Virtual Deep Dive: Accelerate Photonics with Ansys Cloud Burst Compute
events.notes: Learn how Ansys Cloud Burst Compute integrates directly with Lumerical to deliver faster turnaround times, flexible compute choices, and a seamless path from job submission to results.

events.title: AI Training Data Generation, Management, and Reuse with SPDM, PIDO, and HPC
events.notes: Discover how to use Ansys optiSLang and Ansys Minerva for AI Training Data Generation, management, and Reuse with SPDM, PIDO, and HPC.

events.title: Democratizing Simulation and AI-Powered Apps for SPDM and PIDO
events.notes: Learn even more tips and tricks on using Ansys optiSLang and Minerva foron AI Training Data Generation, Management, and Reuse with SPDM, PIDO, and HPC.

events.title: Closing the Process Chain with Envyo
events.notes: Envyo automates data transfer and material assignment in LS-DYNA projects, simplifying simulation workflows. Learn how it improves consistency and speeds up results.

events.title: From Concept to Reality: Robotic Simulation with Ansys Structural Tools
events.notes: Structural simulation is crucial in designing modern robots, ensuring they are functional, safe, and durable. Ansys provides tools for comprehensive system-level modeling of robotic components.

events.title: Engineering Resilient Space Systems: Electronic Reliability
events.notes: Ansys Sherlock enhances reliability predictions for space electronics, providing insights into PCB and component-level risk analysis for mission success.

events.title: Detecting Threat Signatures
events.notes: Learn how to use physics-based solver numerics including computational fluid dynamics, electromagnetics, and ray tracing to accurately determine a vehicle’s infra-red and radar cross section signatures. (U.S. persons only)

events.title: A&D Autonomy - Digital Engineering for Advanced Air Mobility
events.notes: Explore how autonomy, MBSE, and simulation are transforming Advanced Air Mobility and accelerating eVTOL development with digital validation and synthetic data.

events.title: Software Reliability for Space: A Model-Based Approach with SCADE and STK
events.notes: Learn how to use Ansys SCADE for model-based development, automated code generation, and verification, featuring a live Satellite Attitude Controller case.

events.title: Tracking Layer Sensor Simulation - EOIR and Radar
events.notes: Evaluate sensors against multiple criteria including time to detection and performance. Learn about simulating sensor outputs and generating synthetic scenes to train operators and AI algorithms. (U.S. persons only)

events.title: Advanced Optimization Techniques for Electric Machine Design
events.notes: Explore how you can leverage Ansys optiSLang and Ansys Motor-CAD integration for efficient design exploration and performance improvement.

events.title: Getting Started with Thermal Analysis in Ansys Mechanical
events.notes: Discover how engineers use thermal analysis to improve performance and reliability — join this Foundational Fridays webinar for an introduction to heat transfer simulation and its real-world application.
